title: Population in Sweden 2018 , by level of education
summary: This is a bar chart. It shows Share of population for 8 number of Level Of Educations.
The maximum Share of population 23.4 is found at Level Of Education Upper secondary education (3 years or more) and the minimum is found at Post-graduate education where Level Of Education is 1.12.
There is a difference of 22.28 between the maximum Level Of Education Upper secondary education (3 years or more) and minimum Level Of Education Post-graduate education.
min_summary: This is a bar chart representing Level Of Education in the x axis and Share of population in the y axis.
Level Of Education Upper secondary education (3 years or more) has the highest Share of population and Post-graduate education has the lowest Share of population.

max_summary: This is a bar chart. It shows Share of population for 8 number of Level Of Educations.
The Share of population is appeared to be the highest at Level Of Education Upper secondary education (3 years or more) and lowest at Level Of Education Post-graduate education.
Level Of Education Post-secondary education (3 years or more) has the second highest value for Share of population.
The difference of Share of population between the highest and lowest Level Of Education is 22.28.

Share of population at Level Of Education Upper secondary education (3 years or more) is 23.4 , second place is Post-secondary education (3 years or more) at 21.7, and thirdly is Upper secondary education (less than 3 years) at 19.5.
The lowest value 1.12 at Post-graduate education is almost 1.87 times smaller than the average value 12.52.
Summing up the values of all Level Of Educations, we get total 100.12.
